description: She/Her   Tiny Canadian artist/Tattoo artist, #LFC supporter, #actuallyautistic, just trying my best
tweet: There is more but thatâ€™s all I feel like writing. Tbh I have very mixed feelings. And since itâ€™s autism acceptance month, I just ask for patience and understanding. I will screw up, a lot.  And apologize ahead of time for it.

name: Kristin Wilkinson
description: She/Her   Tiny Canadian artist/Tattoo artist, #LFC supporter, #actuallyautistic, just trying my best
tweet: Despite my difficulties Iâ€™ve been professionally successful. Before my current career I was working in veterinary medicine (vetâ€™s assistant) and had considered going on further, but it was a very emotional job and I was unable to handle that. So I left to pursue tattooing.

name: Kristin Wilkinson
description: She/Her   Tiny Canadian artist/Tattoo artist, #LFC supporter, #actuallyautistic, just trying my best
tweet: I am overly emphatic and I have a very fixed view on what is right/wrong and what is fair. I often cry when I hear or see stories in the news. For example, Iâ€™m a vegetarian, and have been for many years, and will probably remain one for the rest of my life.

name: Kristin Wilkinson
description: She/Her   Tiny Canadian artist/Tattoo artist, #LFC supporter, #actuallyautistic, just trying my best
tweet: Despite my difficulty handling stress I am able to keep a cool head in a crisis...contradictory I know but itâ€™s true. Iâ€™ve known what to do in a medical emergency before and am thankful for that

name: Kristin Wilkinson
description: She/Her   Tiny Canadian artist/Tattoo artist, #LFC supporter, #actuallyautistic, just trying my best
tweet: Perks tho. I know it helps me with my art. I can see the world differently, and I know that helps me draw/paint. I donâ€™t know how, but it does. And I have a fantastic memory which helps me with details (I would do very well on Jeopardy). I am full of useless facts/info lol.

name: Kristin Wilkinson
description: She/Her   Tiny Canadian artist/Tattoo artist, #LFC supporter, #actuallyautistic, just trying my best
tweet: And I have my routines and itâ€™s so important to me that I keep them. If anything changes last minute I meltdown. I will pace, I get angry, I cry.

name: Kristin Wilkinson
description: She/Her   Tiny Canadian artist/Tattoo artist, #LFC supporter, #actuallyautistic, just trying my best
tweet: But itâ€™s ok. Because I have my comforts. I will watch movies/tv shoes over and over again if I love them. And I will play the same song on repeat for hours and days. Hyperfixation itâ€™s called. When I say I love something, I love the hell out of it.

name: Kristin Wilkinson
description: She/Her   Tiny Canadian artist/Tattoo artist, #LFC supporter, #actuallyautistic, just trying my best
tweet: I am very impulsive, and that often goes along with my moods. I will confess I am difficult, very difficult, this I know. And for this reason I prefer to keep to myself

name: Kristin Wilkinson
description: She/Her   Tiny Canadian artist/Tattoo artist, #LFC supporter, #actuallyautistic, just trying my best
tweet: Iâ€™m like that in real life as well. If Iâ€™m too stressed out, or if Iâ€™m being yelled at or Iâ€™m in trouble, or if thereâ€™s too much noise I shutdown. I forget how to speak, or what to do.

name: Kristin Wilkinson
description: She/Her   Tiny Canadian artist/Tattoo artist, #LFC supporter, #actuallyautistic, just trying my best
tweet: I do get overwhelmed often. Especially if I get too many messages/comments/emails. I see them all, and I feel my mind start to go blank and I go mute. So if I donâ€™t reply itâ€™s more that my brain is overloading and I forget how to properly communicate.

name: Kristin Wilkinson
description: She/Her   Tiny Canadian artist/Tattoo artist, #LFC supporter, #actuallyautistic, just trying my best
tweet: Iâ€™m autistic. And I have adhd as well, and I suffer from severe anxiety and depression. Yeah. lol. Itâ€™s a constant struggle no lie but it is what it is.

name: Kristin Wilkinson
description: She/Her   Tiny Canadian artist/Tattoo artist, #LFC supporter, #actuallyautistic, just trying my best
tweet: I am not the most articulate so forgive me if i at any point sound confusing. I am not always capable of properly expressing my thoughts and ideas...which goes hand in hand with this I think...sorry I am rambling
